{"item_id": 2360, "title": "Banish All Natural Fungicide Downey & Powdery Mildew Control Proprietary Mixture of Powerful Natural Geraniol 1 Gallon Concentrate Mixes to 960 Gallons of Non-Toxic Spray", "category": "Industrial_and_Scientific", "description": "BANISH by Supreme Growers is the purest concentrate on the Powdery mildew control market - 1 gallon size makes 960 gallons of ready to use product - BANISH is a 100% all natural fungicide for powdery & downey downy mildew treatment - safe for all crops and stages of growth. SHAKE VIGOROUSLY BEFORE EACH USE!
BANISH is a concentrated natural organicide formulated with a diverse blend of powerful plant oils that treats the root of fungal disease with specific modes of action. Banish has a Patented Micronization process that takes these normally bulky, heavy oils and shrinks them down to less than 1 micron in size.
BANISH is extremely effective, both on contact and preventative control. Composed of Gerinol and Iso Alcohol. The Gerinol prevents the translocation of positive charged Potassium ions through the downy powdery mildew, which is how this fungus spreads. The micronized gerinol particles get into the vascular tissue of the plant, where the mildew s hyphae are anchored in. This kills the fungi at the source where it is anchored into the plant.
BANISH also creates a layer on the plant so other mildew spores cannot germinate on contact. The alcohol helps dry out the fungal layer on the surface of the plant to insure a rapid rate of death so the mildew doesn t shoot a ton of spores out before it dies. This duo is mildew s worst nightmare. The Geraniol in BANISH is the purest available, Non-GMO, We source our oils from Asia to guarantee the highest level of quality.
BANISH is fully registered and positioned for all sectors of agriculture. Under warm conditions, BANISH will naturally biodegrade leaving minimal to no residue. Perfect for vegetables, fruits, flowers, plants, trees, medical cannabis marijuana etc. Click Add to Cart to order BANISH now. At Supreme Growers, we believe that quality starts at the soil. Our mission is to equip growers with the knowledge and resources to make self-sustainable growing economically viable. Thats our commitment
CONTROLS VARIOUS DOWNY & POWDERY MILDEW PATHOGENS BANISH uses natural geranium oil plant extract as a fungicide. Mildew growth cycles begin with spore germination at the plant surface. After docking at the surface, mildew germ tubes begin to grow and feed from plant cell nutrients. The two fold prevention and healing effect works by inhibiting spore germination, germ tube growth, and by destroying the pathogen cell. Geraniol induces an unbalance of potassium K+ ions inside the mycelium and inhibits mildew spore germination and mycelium growth. It enters the pathogen cell, causing cell lyses or cell death. Dilute 4.0 mL of BANISH per 1 gallon of water. BANISH should be foliar sprayed directly onto the mildew outbreak and areas affected by powdery or downy mildew. To reduce the chance of burning, raise grow lamps and do not use directly under intense lighting. If outdoors, do not apply during peak sun, apply during the morning or evening. Apply to infected areas 2 - 4 times every 5 - 7 days apart. To prevent mildew outbreaks, apply BANISH every 14 days.

{"item_id": 2367, "title": "Koyo NTA-1625 Needle Roller and Cage Thrust Assembly, Open, Steel Cage, Inch, 1" ID, 1-9/16" OD, 5/64" Width, 11000rpm Maximum Rotational Speed, 12100lbf Static Load Capacity, 3110lbf Dynamic Load Capacity", "category": "Industrial_and_Scientific", "description": "Thrust needle roller and cage assembly for applications with high dynamic loads
High axial load capacity with reduced cross-section for use in restricted spaces
Steel cage guides and evenly spaces rollers for reduced friction, vibration, and noise
Through-hardened, high-carbon chromium steel rollers for heat tolerance and durability under heavy loads
Meets ANSI ABMA standard 21.2 for quality assurance
This Koyo thrust needle roller and cage assembly has a steel cage and is suitable for applications with high dynamic axial loads. It has a smaller cross-section than a standard thrust bearing for use in restricted spaces. The cage provides guidance and even spacing of the rollers for reduced friction, vibration, and noise when operated at high speeds, and it is made of hardened steel for greater strength, rigidity, and heat resistance than nylon cages. The needle rollers are made of through-hardened, high-carbon chromium steel for durability and heat tolerance under heavy loads, and have contoured ends to optimize the distribution of contact stress. This thrust needle roller and cage assembly meets American National Standards Institute American Bearing Manufacturers Association standard ANSI ABMA 21.2 for quality assurance, and is used in various applications, such as automotive and truck transmissions, agricultural and construction equipment, pumps and compressors, and two-cycle engines, among others.
Roller bearings use rolling elements to maintain a separation between moving parts to reduce rotational friction and support radial and axial loads. These elements can be one of the following types ball, cylindrical, spherical, barrel, needle, spindle, or tapered. Roller bearings can be open on both ends a shaft can pass through or open on one end and closed on the other. An open end can be sealed or shielded to protect the bearing from solid contaminants and moisture that could reduce its lifespan. If an end is sealed, the sealing component is an elastomer lip that contacts the shaft. If it is shielded, the shielding is a non-contact lip, usually made of metal. Rolling bearings are used in a range of applications from agricultural machinery to conveying equipment, robotics, dental equipment, elevators, rolling mills, ship rudder shafts, and aggregate crushers, among others.
Koyo Bearings USA manufactures needle roller bearings, bearing assemblies, and needle rollers for automotive and industrial applications. The company, founded in 2009, is headquartered in Canton, OH, and meets International Organization for Standardization ISO standards 14001 and TS 16949 for quality assurance.

{"item_id": 2368, "title": "Starrett Caliper with High-Grade Steel Legs and Improved Joint Design for Tension Adjustment - 6" Size and Capacity, Firm-Joint Type, Flat Leg Style - 27-6", "category": "Industrial_and_Scientific", "description": "Ergonomic - The Caliper is light, comfortable, easy to use and constructed with features that have made Starrett calipers the machinist s first choice for many years.
Made From Robust Materials - Starrett tools are durable and made from quality materials, The legs are designed from a high-grade steel, well-finished and ruggedly constructed.
Easy to Use - Incorporating convenience and excellence, Starrett tools are designed to be user-friendly. Whether you re an experienced professional or an amateur when it comes to home improvement, our tools are handy and accessible.
Quality Tool - It has an improved joint designed for tension adjustment and ensures that the tension will not change with leg movement.
Meets Strong Demands - Committed in providing customers with consistent and reliable solutions, Starrett has set the standard for precision, quality and innovation. Our products are long-lasting, robust with excellent service and performance.
The Starrett 27-6 improved firm-joint inside caliper has a leg length of 6 150 mm but opens to approximately one-third larger than the leg length. The joint allows for tension adjustment, while the tension will not change if the legs move. The legs are made from a high-grade steel and are ruggedly constructed and well-finished.
Calipers measure the distance between two opposing sides of an object. They make inside, outside, depth, or step measurements, according to their type. Calipers are commonly used in architecture, metalworking, mechanical engineering, machining, manufacturing, carpentry, and medicine. The simplest calipers have two legs to mark the two points and require a ruler to take the measurement. More complex calipers use two sets of jaws instead of legs and have up to two graduated scales. Vernier, dial, and digital calipers give direct and accurate readings and are functionally identical, having a calibrated scale with a fixed jaw, and another jaw with a movable pointer that slides along the scale. The vernier caliper has a scale sliding parallel to the main scale for an additional, fractional reading to improve measurement precision. The dial caliper has a circular dial with a pointer on a toothed gear rack replacing the second vernier scale. As with the vernier, this second measurement is added to the reading from the main scale to obtain the result. The dial caliper is used also for measuring size differential between two objects. The digital caliper takes the same sort of differential measurements as the dial caliper by zeroing the display at any point along the slide, with an LCD replacing the dial that displays a single, easily read value in both English and metric units. Some digital calipers can hold data readings between measurements and send them to data collection devices.
The L. S. Starrett Company was founded in 1880, originally manufacturing bench vises, squares, and other tools. It has an adjustable VOP velocity of propagation setting to optimize the accuracy of fault location and cable length measurements. The test set has two basic modes of operation talk mode for off-hook operations including verifying dialing and receiving calls, and monitor mode for on-hook operations including checking for an idle line, listening for line noise, measuring DC voltage on the line, and capturing DTMF dual-tone multi-frequency tones to check for proper signaling. In monitor mode, the test set provides a high impedance coupling to monitor lines without disrupting service. When switching to talk mode, the data lockout feature tests the line for high-speed data signals and remains on hook and beeps if such signals are detected. The lockout can be overridden to pull dial tone from a noise line. Telephone test sets, also called butt sets, are used by telecom technicians to troubleshoot and maintain copper-wire voice-subscriber lines such as POTS plain old telephone service lines. A carriage bolt, coach bolt or round head square neck bolt is a form of bolt used to fasten metal to wood. It is distinguished from other bolts by its shallow mushroom head and that the shank cross-section of the bolt is circular for most of its length, as usual, but the portion immediately beneath the head is formed into a square section. This makes the bolt self-locking when placed through a square hole in a metal strap, or a round hole in most wood. This allows the fastener to be installed with only a single tool, a spanner or wrench, working from one side. The head of a carriage bolt is usually a shallow dome. The squared section is of the same size as the diameter of the bolt shank, with a plain unthreaded shank. Carriage bolts were developed for use through iron strengthening plates on either side of a wooden beam. It is commonplace though to use them to bare timber, the squared section giving enough grip to prevent rotation.

This type of slide gate valve was originally designed for draining tanks and controlling shallow bodies of water like ponds and lagoons. They can also be used as shut off valves in low pressure or vacuum air lines. Please note that each valve size has an open and closed pressure rating. Because the plastic paddle can flex with flowing water they are not good for throttling water or trying to close the valve with fast moving water  thus the low mid flow cut off water pressure of approximately 6 pounds per square inch psi . These slide valves are sometimes referred to as knife or guillotine gate valves and are a great alternative to ball valves in low pressure applications since they are full flow, quick opening, and are generally a much lower cost especially in larger sizes. They work well with soft debris like waste but small hard debris can settle in the bottom of the valve seat slot and prevent it from closing completely. They can easily be cleaned or repaired by unbolting and replacing the seals or valve body. The handles simply unscrew for easy replacement  if you do so be sure not to damage the valve shaft. Extension rods are available for remote actuation. The Valterra 7101 gate valve has 1-1 2 Schedule 40 female slip fittings which receive 1-1 2 pipe. Black acrylonitrile butadiene styrene ABS body and hub fittings are resistant to corrosion and mild chemicals as are the polypropolene PP paddle and thermoplastic vulcanizate TPV seals. The valve shaft is made of 304 stainless steel. Hardware is zinc plated steel. It has a maximum pressure rating of 45 psi in the closed position, 30 psi in the open position, and a mid-flow maximum closing pressure rating of 6 psi. The maximum temperature rating is 205 degrees F 96 degrees C . See Gate Valve Measurement chart for dimensions and Head Pressure chart for determining the pressure based on the height of water being held back.

It also can be used as a location guide. Alloy steel is often used in applications where strength is the primary consideration.
Pins are non-threaded cylindrical fasteners that are inserted into one or more holes to fix a component s position, join components, or maintain alignment between them. Several different pin styles fit a variety of application and installation requirements. Dowel pins, for example, have a solid shaft that is often rounded or beveled at the ends. Quick-release pins have a button, handle, or ring at one end that releases retractable balls at the other end to act as a lock-and-release mechanism. Clevis pins have a head at one end and one or more cross holes at the other end that allow insertion of cotter pins to lock components in place. Cotter pins have two prongs that can be inserted into the hole of clevis pins or other fasteners and bent to secure them in place.
